New methods
(*) equalsIgnoreCase()
similar to equals method but ignore the cases
takes: String
return boolean
ex:

String str = "Java";
str.equalsIgnoreCase("java")--> true

(*)indexOf()

> gives the index of the passed string(first occurance)

if the given string is not found the object string the result is -1

takes: String
return: int (index)
ex:

String str = "Java"
str.indexOf("va")--> 2
str.indexOf("a")---> 1
str.indexOf("vo")----> -1

(*) lastIndexOf()
>smilar of indexOf method , except it gives the last occyrance of the String

> ex:

String str = "Java"
str.lastIndexOf("a")----> 3

Note: The following methods will need assigned to a new variable or resigned to the existing one OR use the result right away


(*) toLowerCase()
will trun all characters in the string to lowercases
>will trun all characters in the string to  lowercase
take: String
> return String
ex:
String str = "Java";
str = str.tolowerCase()----> "java"

(*) toUpperCase()
will trun all characters in the string to lowercases
>will trun all characters in the string to  lowercase
take: String
> return String
ex:
String str = "Java";
str = str2.tolowerCase()----> "JAVA"

(*) repalce()
> Give back a string with every occurnace of the old character repalce with the caracter 
> takes : two char ( oldChar, newChar)
return: String
ex:
String str = "Java"
str= str.repalce('a','0')---> Jovo


(*) Substring
>Give back part of a String based on the given index
takes: int(index)
return:String

ex:

String str = "Java"
String str2 = str.substring(2)---> "va"
String str3 = str.substring(3)---> "a"


(*) substring()
> takes: two numbers/ indexes ( start, end)
returns: String in that range - NOT include the last index
ex:
String str = "Java";
str = substring(1,3)-----> "av"









